Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_gate_array_filler(25.10)                      add_gate_array_filler(25.10)

Name
       add_gate_array_filler  -  Inserts  GA filler cells with regular pattern
       during the pre-place stage

Syntax
       add_gate_array_filler

       [-help]

       [-allow_shift_distance <x> <y>]

       [-area <x1> <y1> <x2> <y2>]

       [-cell_orientation {R0|MX|MY|R180}]

       [-min_spacing_x <distance>]

       [-min_spacing_y <distance>]

       [-offsetx <offset_in_microns>]

       [-offsety <offset_in_microns>]

       [-powerDomain <powerDomainName>]

       [-prefix <prefixName>]

       {-cell <cellName> -stepx <step_in_microns> -stepy <step_in_microns>}

       Inserts GA filler cells  with  regular  pattern  during  the  pre-place
       stage.  While  inserting  the GA filler, the command ensures that every
       boundary channel has at least one column GA filler.

       The GA filler cells created by this command are marked as physical-only
       cells. This means that the isPhysOnly  attribute  of  these  GA  filler
       cells  is  set  to  true.  This  is  a  prerequisite  for  the ecoPlace
       -useGAFillerCells command to map the unplaced ECO cells to the added GA
       filler cells, in case of a GA filler-based post-mask ECO.

Parameters
       -allow_shift_distance <x> <y>
              Specifies the distance between the new and the original position
              in the x and y directions.

              If you do not specify -allow_shift_distance, the GA filler  will
              be removed if it is added at original location with a violation.
              If  -allow_shift_distance is specified, the GA can be shifted to
              avoid violation. If a GA filler cannot be added at the  original
              location  because of the violation, it will be moved to the left
              side, right side, upside, or downside of the  original  location
              to  ensure that there is no violation. The next filler keeps the
              step value with the original position of the moved filler.

       -area <x1 y1 x2 y2>
              Specifies the area in which GA fillers are to be inserted. If no
              area is specified, GA fillers will be inserted for the  complete
              core area.

       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the name of the filler cell to be used.

       -cell_orientation {R0|MX|MY|R180}
              Specifies all legal orientations of GFILL instances.

       -min_spacing_x <distance>
              Specifies  the distance between edges of GA fillers in the hori-
              zontal direction. The following diagram shows min spacing  is  X
              and Y from Cell A. No other GA filler can touch the red box.

       -min_spacing_y <distance>
              Specifies the distance between edges of GA fillers in the verti-
              cal  direction. The following diagram shows min spacing is X and
              Y from Cell A. No other GA filler can touch the red box.

       -offsetx <offset_in_microns>
              Specifies the offset, in microns, from the origin in  the  hori-
              zontal  direction. If the -area parameter is specified, the ori-
              gin is (x1, y1) of the box defined by  -area. If  -area  is  not
              specified the origin is (0,0).

       -offsety <offset_in_microns>
              Specifies  the offset, in microns, from the origin in the verti-
              cal direction. If the -area parameter is specified,  the  origin
              is (x1, y1) of the box defined by  -area. If  -area is not spec-
              ified the origin is (0,0).

       -powerDomain powerDomainName
              Specifies the power domain for which fillers are to be inserted.

       -prefix <prefixName>
              Specifies the prefix for the inserted GA filler cells.

       -stepx <step_in_microns>
              Specifies  the distance between GA fillers in the horizontal di-
              rection.

       -stepy <step_in_microns>
              Specifies the distance between GA fillers in the vertical direc-
              tion

Examples
              * The following command adds GA fillers  of  type  GAFILL4  with
                spacing  in  horizontal  and vertical direction of 20 microns.
                The first GAFILL4 will be placed at (10, 0).

                add_gate_array_filler -cell GAFILL4 -stepx 20 -stepy 20  -off-
                setx 10

              * The  following  command  adds  GA fillers of type GAFILL4 with
                regular spacing 20 and start location (0, 0).

                add_gate_array_filler -cell GAFILL4 -stepx 20 -stepy 20

              *

                The following command adds GA fillers  of  type  GAFILL4  with
                vertical  and horizontal spacing of 10 microns in the area de-
                fined by coordinates 100 100 500 500.

                add_gate_array_filler -area 100  100  500  500  -cell  GAFILL4
                -stepx 10 -stepy 10

